cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep learning models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for defensive techniques to detect and mitigate these attacks, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed method, UnMask, is based on robust feature alignment, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
